SECTION_CONTENT:
Eye Contact
Rinse immediately with plenty of water, also under the eyelids, for at least 15 minutes.
Obtain medical attention.
Skin Contact
Wash off immediately with plenty of water for at least 15 minutes. Get medical attention
immediately if symptoms occur.
Inhalation
Move to fresh air. If breathing is difficult, give oxygen. Get medical attention immediately if
symptoms occur.
Ingestion
Do not induce vomiting. Obtain medical attention.
Most important symptoms/effects
Causes eye burns.
Notes to Physician
Treat symptomatically
